    <section class="features">
        <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">01</div>
            <h3>PREAMP SATURATION</h3>
            <p>Modeled on the high-gain input stage of vintage analog gear. The <strong>DRIVE</strong> knob pushes the signal into warm harmonic distortion before it even hits the spring.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">02</div>
            <h3>PHYSICAL TENSION</h3>
            <p>Unlike standard algorithmic reverbs, the <strong>DECAY</strong> control simulates the physical tension of the metal coils, creating authentic "boing" and dispersion artifacts.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">03</div>
            <h3>SELF-OSCILLATION</h3>
            <p>Push the <strong>FEEDBACK</strong> past 90% to trigger the feedback loop. Create infinite dub sirens and runaway noise washes without external hardware.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">04</div>
            <h3>DUB TONE STACK</h3>
            <p>A specialized EQ circuit (<strong>BASS / TREBLE</strong>) sits inside the wet signal path, allowing you to darken the tails for that murky, underwater classic dub sound.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">05</div>
            <h3>METERING</h3>
            <p>High-resolution 18-segment LED meters for Input and Output levels, behind glass for precise gain staging in dark studios.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">06</div>
            <h3>CPU OPTIMIZED</h3>
            <p>Engineered with C++ architecture for zero-latency performance. Ideal for live tracking or dense mixes, ensuring rock-solid stability without taxing your CPU.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="architecture">
        <div class="arch-container">
